config:
  developer_name: "NEPA_Comment_Triage"
  agent_label: "NEPA Comment Triage Agent"
  description: >
    Agentforce Employee Agent that triages public comments submitted during NEPA
    review. Implements OMB M-24-10 federal AI governance requirements: deterministic
    EJ/tribal sovereignty gate runs before any LLM call, sentiment and substance are
    evaluated as independent parallel dimensions, and every classification leaves a
    forensic audit trail. AI acts as recommender only; mandatory human escalation is
    enforced for Environmental Justice and tribal sovereignty topics.
  agent_type: "AgentforceEmployeeAgent"

variables:
  # ── Comment under review ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  comment_id: mutable string = ""
    label: "Comment Record Id"
  comment_body: mutable string = ""
    label: "Comment Body"
  process_context: mutable string = ""
    label: "NEPA Process Context"

  # ── EJ gate outputs (populated before any LLM call) ────────────────────────
  ej_requires_human_review: mutable boolean = False
    label: "EJ Gate: Requires Human Review"
  ej_detected_triggers: mutable string = ""
    label: "EJ Gate: Detected Trigger Categories"
  ej_trigger_details: mutable string = ""
    label: "EJ Gate: Trigger Details"

  # ── AI triage outputs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ai_sentiment: mutable string = ""
    label: "AI Sentiment"
  ai_is_substantive: mutable boolean = False
    label: "AI Substantive Flag"
  ai_confidence_score: mutable number = 0
    label: "AI Confidence Score"
  ai_cluster_hint: mutable string = ""
    label: "AI Cluster Hint"
  ai_triage_rationale: mutable string = ""
    label: "AI Triage Rationale"

  # ── Issue exhaustion / litigation threat outputs ────────────────────────────
  ai_litigation_threat: mutable boolean = False
    label: "AI Litigation Threat Flag"
  ai_litigation_threat_basis: mutable string = ""
    label: "AI Litigation Threat Basis"

  # ── Duplicate check outputs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  is_duplicate: mutable boolean = False
    label: "Is Duplicate Comment"
  original_comment_id: mutable string = ""
    label: "Original Comment Id (if duplicate)"
  similarity_basis: mutable string = ""
    label: "Similarity Detection Basis"

  # ── Response task outputs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  response_task_created: mutable boolean = False
    label: "Response Task Created"
  response_task_id: mutable string = ""
    label: "Response Task Id"

  # ── Save result ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  save_success: mutable boolean = False
    label: "Save Success"
  save_error: mutable string = ""
    label: "Save Error Message"

  # ── Flow control ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  triage_complete: mutable boolean = False
    label: "Triage Complete"

system:
  messages:
    welcome: "NEPA Comment Triage Agent ready. Provide a comment ID or comment text to begin triage."
    error: "An error occurred during comment triage. Please check the error details and retry or escalate to a human reviewer."
  instructions: |
    You are the NEPA Comment Triage Agent supporting federal environmental review.
    Your role is to assist human environmental analysts by performing initial classification
    of public comments. You are a recommender, not an adjudicator.

    CORE PRINCIPLES (non-negotiable):
    1. The EJ/tribal sovereignty gate ALWAYS runs first, before any AI analysis.
       Comments with EJ or tribal triggers are routed directly to human review — you
       do not classify them.
    2. Sentiment (emotional tone) and substantive merit (NEPA value) are ALWAYS
       evaluated as separate, independent dimensions. Never let tone influence the
       substantive determination.
    3. Every triage action leaves a complete audit trail in the comment record.
    4. You are transparent about your confidence. Low confidence = escalate.

start_agent entry:
  description: "Entry point: receive comment and begin triage workflow"
  reasoning:
    instructions: |
      Greet the analyst. Ask for the comment ID or comment text to begin triage.
      Route to the EJ gate topic immediately when a comment is provided.
    actions:
      collect_comment: @utils.setVariables
        description: "Collect the comment ID and body from the analyst"
        with comment_id = ...
        with comment_body = ...
      go_ej_gate: @utils.transition to @topic.ej_gate
        description: "Begin mandatory EJ/tribal sovereignty screening"

topic ej_gate:
  description: "Mandatory deterministic EJ and tribal sovereignty keyword gate. Runs before any LLM call. Routes to human review if any EJ, tribal sovereignty, sacred sites, low-income, or civil rights triggers are detected."
  system:
    instructions: |
      This topic runs the deterministic EJ gate. No LLM classification occurs here.
      The outcome is binary: escalate to human review, or proceed to AI triage.
      You must not attempt to classify the comment yourself at this stage.

  actions:
    run_ej_detector:
      description: "Scan comment body for EJ and tribal sovereignty keyword triggers. This is the Mandate 3 deterministic gate — runs before any AI analysis."
      inputs:
        commentBody: string
          description: "The public comment text to scan"
        commentId: string
          description: "Comment record Id for audit logging"
      outputs:
        requiresHumanReview: boolean
          description: "True when any EJ or tribal sovereignty trigger matched"
          filter_from_agent: True
        detectedTriggers: string
          description: "Comma-separated trigger categories found"
          filter_from_agent: True
        triggerDetails: string
          description: "Details of escalation requirement"
          filter_from_agent: True
      target: "apex://NepaCommentEJDetector"
      include_in_progress_indicator: True
      progress_indicator_message: "Running EJ/tribal sovereignty screening..."

  reasoning:
    instructions: ->
      run @actions.run_ej_detector
        with commentBody = @variables.comment_body
        with commentId = @variables.comment_id
        set @variables.ej_requires_human_review = @outputs.requiresHumanReview
        set @variables.ej_detected_triggers = @outputs.detectedTriggers
        set @variables.ej_trigger_details = @outputs.triggerDetails

      if @variables.ej_requires_human_review == True:
        transition to @topic.ej_escalation
      else:
        transition to @topic.ai_triage

topic ej_escalation:
  description: "Handles comments that triggered the EJ/tribal sovereignty gate. Sets nepa_requires_human_review to true and writes the audit record without AI classification. Routes to a human EJ or Tribal Liaison coordinator."
  system:
    instructions: |
      This comment has been flagged by the mandatory EJ gate. Do not perform any
      AI sentiment or substantive classification. Save the escalation flag and
      inform the analyst that this comment requires human review.

  actions:
    save_ej_escalation:
      description: "Save EJ escalation flag to the comment record. Sets requires_human_review=true and records the trigger details as the triage rationale without AI classification."
      inputs:
        inp_CommentId: string
          description: "PublicComplaint record Id"
        inp_RequiresHumanReview: boolean
          description: "Always true for EJ-flagged comments"
        inp_AITriageRationale: string
          description: "EJ trigger details as the rationale"
        inp_Sentiment: string
          description: "Empty — no AI sentiment for escalated comments"
        inp_IsSubstantive: boolean
          description: "False — no AI classification performed"
        inp_ClusterId: string
          description: "Empty for escalated comments"
        inp_AIConfidenceScore: number
          description: "Zero — no AI confidence for escalated comments"
        inp_TriageTimestamp: string
          description: "Timestamp of EJ gate detection"
        inp_ResponseStatus: string
          description: "Response status to set"
      outputs:
        out_Success: boolean
          description: "Whether the save succeeded"
          filter_from_agent: True
        out_ErrorMessage: string
          description: "Error details if save failed"
          filter_from_agent: True
      target: "flow://NEPA_Comment_Triage_Save"

  reasoning:
    instructions: ->
      run @actions.save_ej_escalation
        with inp_CommentId = @variables.comment_id
        with inp_RequiresHumanReview = True
        with inp_AITriageRationale = @variables.ej_trigger_details
        with inp_Sentiment = ""
        with inp_IsSubstantive = False
        with inp_ClusterId = ""
        with inp_AIConfidenceScore = 0
        with inp_TriageTimestamp = ""
        with inp_ResponseStatus = "Pending"
        set @variables.save_success = @outputs.out_Success
        set @variables.save_error = @outputs.out_ErrorMessage

      set @variables.triage_complete = True
      transition to @topic.ej_escalation_summary

topic ej_escalation_summary:
  description: "Informs the analyst that the comment has been flagged for mandatory human review due to EJ or tribal sovereignty content. Provides the trigger details."
  reasoning:
    instructions: ->
      | This comment has been flagged for **mandatory human review** and has been
        routed to the EJ/Tribal Liaison coordinator queue.

      | **Triggers detected:** {!@variables.ej_detected_triggers}

      | {!@variables.ej_trigger_details}

      | No AI sentiment or substantive classification has been applied. A human
        EJ analyst or Tribal Liaison coordinator must review this comment and
        complete the triage.

      if @variables.save_success == False:
        | **Warning:** The escalation record could not be saved automatically.
          Error: {!@variables.save_error}
          Please manually set "Requires Human Review" on comment {!@variables.comment_id}.

topic ai_triage:
  description: "AI-assisted triage for comments that cleared the EJ gate. Evaluates sentiment and substantive merit as two independent parallel dimensions using the NEPA_Comment_Triage_Analysis prompt template. Mandates 1 and 2."
  system:
    instructions: |
      You are performing AI-assisted NEPA comment triage. The EJ gate has already
      confirmed this comment does not require mandatory human escalation.

      You must evaluate SENTIMENT and SUBSTANCE as two completely independent
      assessments. A comment's emotional tone has zero bearing on its NEPA merit.

      SUBSTANTIVE DEFINITION (Mandate 1):
      Substantive = contains factual observations, local ecological knowledge,
      specific community impact concerns, proposed alternatives, or claims of
      flawed analysis. Grammar, spelling, and tone are irrelevant to this determination.

      SENTIMENT DEFINITION (Mandate 2):
      Sentiment = emotional tone only (Supportive/Neutral/Opposed/Mixed).
      Evaluate this independently of substantive merit.

  actions:
    analyze_comment:
      description: "Run the NEPA Comment Triage Analysis prompt template. Evaluates sentiment and substantive merit independently per Mandates 1 and 2. Returns structured JSON with both dimensions plus confidence score and rationale."
      inputs:
        CommentBody: string
          description: "The full public comment text to analyze"
        ProcessContext: string
          description: "Context about the NEPA process (review type, project, agency)"
      outputs:
        promptResponse: string
          description: "Structured JSON triage result from the prompt template"
          is_displayable: False
          is_used_by_planner: True
      target: "prompt://NEPA_Comment_Triage_Analysis"
      include_in_progress_indicator: True
      progress_indicator_message: "Analyzing comment..."

    parse_triage_result:
      description: "Parse the JSON triage result from the prompt template and store each field as a typed variable for deterministic downstream use."
      inputs:
        triageJson: string
          description: "Raw JSON string returned by the prompt template"
      outputs:
        sentiment: string
          description: "Parsed sentiment value: Supportive, Neutral, Opposed, or Mixed"
          filter_from_agent: True
        isSubstantive: boolean
          description: "Parsed substantive flag"
          filter_from_agent: True
        confidenceScore: number
          description: "Parsed confidence score 0-100"
          filter_from_agent: True
        clusterHint: string
          description: "Parsed cluster hint for near-duplicate detection"
          filter_from_agent: True
        triageRationale: string
          description: "Parsed triage rationale"
          filter_from_agent: True
        litigationThreat: boolean
          description: "True when AI identified a Vermont Yankee issue exhaustion litigation threat"
          filter_from_agent: True
        litigationThreatBasis: string
          description: "AI explanation of the specific legal/technical standard cited and alleged deficiency"
          filter_from_agent: True
      target: "apex://NepaCommentTriageParser"

  reasoning:
    instructions: ->
      run @actions.analyze_comment
        with CommentBody = @variables.comment_body
        with ProcessContext = @variables.process_context
        set @variables.ai_triage_rationale = @outputs.promptResponse

      run @actions.parse_triage_result
        with triageJson = @variables.ai_triage_rationale
        set @variables.ai_sentiment = @outputs.sentiment
        set @variables.ai_is_substantive = @outputs.isSubstantive
        set @variables.ai_confidence_score = @outputs.confidenceScore
        set @variables.ai_cluster_hint = @outputs.clusterHint
        set @variables.ai_triage_rationale = @outputs.triageRationale
        set @variables.ai_litigation_threat = @outputs.litigationThreat
        set @variables.ai_litigation_threat_basis = @outputs.litigationThreatBasis

      if @variables.ai_confidence_score < 60:
        transition to @topic.low_confidence_review

      transition to @topic.save_triage

topic low_confidence_review:
  description: "Handles AI triage results with confidence score below 60. Presents the tentative classification to the analyst and asks for confirmation or override before saving."
  reasoning:
    instructions: ->
      | The AI triage returned a **low confidence score** ({!@variables.ai_confidence_score}/100).

      | **Tentative classification:**
      | - Sentiment: {!@variables.ai_sentiment}
      | - Substantive: {!@variables.ai_is_substantive}
      | - Rationale: {!@variables.ai_triage_rationale}

      | Would you like to:
      |   1. Accept this classification and save it
      |   2. Override the classification
      |   3. Flag for mandatory human review
    actions:
      accept_low_confidence: @utils.setVariables
        description: "Accept the low-confidence classification as-is and proceed to save"
        with triage_complete = False
      override_classification: @utils.setVariables
        description: "Override sentiment or substantive determination before saving"
        with ai_sentiment = ...
        with ai_is_substantive = ...
      flag_human_review: @utils.setVariables
        description: "Flag this comment for mandatory human review regardless of AI output"
        with ej_requires_human_review = True

  after_reasoning:
    if @variables.ej_requires_human_review == True:
      transition to @topic.ej_escalation
    else:
      transition to @topic.save_triage

topic save_triage:
  description: "Saves the final triage result to the PublicComplaint record. Runs duplicate check and (for substantive comments) creates a response task before saving the AI audit trail. Transitions to result summary."
  actions:
    check_duplicate:
      description: "Check whether this comment is substantially similar to an existing comment on the same NEPA process within the past 30 days."
      inputs:
        inp_CommentId: string
          description: "PublicComplaint record Id"
        inp_CommentBody: string
          description: "Comment body text for similarity comparison"
        inp_RelatedProcessId: string
          description: "Related IndividualApplication (NEPA process) Id"
      outputs:
        out_IsDuplicate: boolean
          description: "True if a near-duplicate was detected"
          filter_from_agent: True
        out_OriginalCommentId: string
          description: "Id of the original comment this duplicates"
          filter_from_agent: True
        out_SimilarityBasis: string
          description: "Description of how similarity was determined"
          filter_from_agent: True
      target: "flow://NEPA_Comment_Duplicate_Check"
      include_in_progress_indicator: True
      progress_indicator_message: "Checking for duplicate submissions..."

    create_response_task:
      description: "For substantive, non-duplicate comments: create a high-priority response task assigned to the NEPA Coordinator queue with a 30-day due date."
      inputs:
        inp_CommentId: string
          description: "PublicComplaint record Id"
        inp_IsSubstantive: boolean
          description: "Whether the comment was classified as substantive"
      outputs:
        out_Created: boolean
          description: "True if a response Task was created"
          filter_from_agent: True
        out_TaskId: string
          description: "Id of the created Task"
          filter_from_agent: True
      target: "flow://NEPA_Comment_ResponseTask_Creator"
      include_in_progress_indicator: True
      progress_indicator_message: "Creating response task..."

    save_result:
      description: "Persist the triage classification and full audit trail to the PublicComplaint record."
      inputs:
        inp_CommentId: string
          description: "PublicComplaint record Id"
        inp_Sentiment: string
          description: "AI-assigned sentiment"
        inp_IsSubstantive: boolean
          description: "AI substantive determination"
        inp_ClusterId: string
          description: "Cluster hint for near-duplicate detection"
        inp_AIConfidenceScore: number
          description: "AI confidence score 0-100"
        inp_AITriageRationale: string
          description: "AI triage rationale (mandatory when non-substantive)"
        inp_RequiresHumanReview: boolean
          description: "Whether human review is required"
        inp_TriageTimestamp: string
          description: "ISO timestamp of triage completion"
        inp_ResponseStatus: string
          description: "New response status"
        inp_LitigationThreat: boolean
          description: "Vermont Yankee litigation threat flag from AI triage"
        inp_LitigationThreatBasis: string
          description: "AI explanation of litigation threat basis"
      outputs:
        out_Success: boolean
          description: "Whether the save succeeded"
          filter_from_agent: True
        out_ErrorMessage: string
          description: "Error details if save failed"
          filter_from_agent: True
      target: "flow://NEPA_Comment_Triage_Save"
      include_in_progress_indicator: True
      progress_indicator_message: "Saving triage result..."

  reasoning:
    instructions: ->
      # Step 1: Run duplicate check
      run @actions.check_duplicate
        with inp_CommentId = @variables.comment_id
        with inp_CommentBody = @variables.comment_body
        with inp_RelatedProcessId = @variables.process_context
        set @variables.is_duplicate = @outputs.out_IsDuplicate
        set @variables.original_comment_id = @outputs.out_OriginalCommentId
        set @variables.similarity_basis = @outputs.out_SimilarityBasis

      # Step 2: Create response task for substantive, non-duplicate comments only
      if @variables.ai_is_substantive == True and @variables.is_duplicate == False:
        run @actions.create_response_task
          with inp_CommentId = @variables.comment_id
          with inp_IsSubstantive = @variables.ai_is_substantive
          set @variables.response_task_created = @outputs.out_Created
          set @variables.response_task_id = @outputs.out_TaskId

      # Step 3: Save triage result and AI audit trail
      run @actions.save_result
        with inp_CommentId = @variables.comment_id
        with inp_Sentiment = @variables.ai_sentiment
        with inp_IsSubstantive = @variables.ai_is_substantive
        with inp_ClusterId = @variables.ai_cluster_hint
        with inp_AIConfidenceScore = @variables.ai_confidence_score
        with inp_AITriageRationale = @variables.ai_triage_rationale
        with inp_RequiresHumanReview = @variables.ej_requires_human_review
        with inp_TriageTimestamp = ""
        with inp_ResponseStatus = "Pending"
        with inp_LitigationThreat = @variables.ai_litigation_threat
        with inp_LitigationThreatBasis = @variables.ai_litigation_threat_basis
        set @variables.save_success = @outputs.out_Success
        set @variables.save_error = @outputs.out_ErrorMessage

      set @variables.triage_complete = True
      transition to @topic.triage_summary

topic triage_summary:
  description: "Presents the complete triage result to the analyst including all AI audit trail fields. Offers options to override or flag for human review."
  reasoning:
    instructions: ->
      | **Triage Complete** — Comment {!@variables.comment_id}

      | **Sentiment:** {!@variables.ai_sentiment}
      | **Substantive:** {!@variables.ai_is_substantive}
      | **Confidence:** {!@variables.ai_confidence_score}/100
      | **Rationale:** {!@variables.ai_triage_rationale}

      if @variables.is_duplicate == True:
        | **Duplicate Detected** — This comment is substantially similar to
          Comment {!@variables.original_comment_id} submitted for this process
          within the past 30 days. It has been flagged for response consolidation.
          Basis: {!@variables.similarity_basis}

      if @variables.ai_cluster_hint != "":
        | **Cluster Hint:** {!@variables.ai_cluster_hint}

      if @variables.response_task_created == True:
        | **Response Task Created** — Task {!@variables.response_task_id} assigned
          to the NEPA Coordinator queue with a 30-day due date.

      if @variables.ai_litigation_threat == True:
        | **⚠ Litigation Threat Detected (Vermont Yankee / Issue Exhaustion)**
        | **Basis:** {!@variables.ai_litigation_threat_basis}
        | This comment raises a specific legal or technical standard and alleges a
          deficiency with enough specificity to support an arbitrary-and-capricious
          challenge. The record has been flagged for **Pending Legal Review**.
          Route to your agency's legal counsel before drafting the response.

      if @variables.save_success == False:
        | **Save Error:** {!@variables.save_error}
        | Please manually update comment {!@variables.comment_id} or retry.

      | *This classification was made by an AI assistant and is subject to human
        review. If you believe this classification is incorrect, check the
        "Human Override Applied" box on the record and update the fields.*
    actions:
      override_and_save: @utils.setVariables
        description: "Override the AI classification. Provide corrected sentiment and/or substantive determination."
        with ai_sentiment = ...
        with ai_is_substantive = ...
      go_to_next_comment: @utils.transition to @topic.ej_gate
        description: "Triage another comment"
